  "name": "Parameters API",
  "description": "In this installment of the API Blueprint course we will discuss how to describe API parameters. \n\nBut first let's add more messages to our system. For that we would need introduce an message identifier â€“ id. This id will be our parameter when communicating with our API about messages. \n\n## API Blueprint\n+ [Previous: Requests](6.%20Requests.md)\n+ [This: Raw API Blueprint](https://raw.github.com/apiaryio/api-blueprint/master/examples/7.%20Parameters.md)\n+ [Next: Headers](8.%20Headers.md)\n\n",
  "resourceGroups": [
    {
      "name": "Messages",
      "description": "Group of all messages-related resources.\n\n",
      "resources": [
        {
          "name": "My Message",
          "description": "Here we have added the message `id` parameter as an [URI Template variable](http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6570) in the Message resource's URI. \nNote the parameter name `id` is enclosed in curly brackets. We will discuss this parameter in the `Parameters` section bellow, where we will also set its example value to `1` and declare it of an arbitrary 'number' type.\n\n",
          "uriTemplate": "/message/{id}",
          "model": {},
          "parameters": {
            "id": {
              "description": "An unique identifier of the message.",
              "type": "number",
              "required": true,
              "default": "",
              "example": "1",
              "values": []
            }
          },
          "headers": {},
          "actions": [
            {
              "name": "Retrieve a Message",
              "description": "",
              "method": "GET",
              "parameters": {},
              "headers": {},
              "examples": [
                {
                  "name": "",
                  "description": "",
                  "requests": [
                    {
                      "name": "Plain Text Message",
                      "description": "",
                      "headers": {
                        "Accept": {
                          "value": "text/plain"
                        }
                      },
                      "body": "",
                      "schema": ""
                    },
                    {
                      "name": "JSON Message",
                      "description": "",
                      "headers": {
                        "Accept": {
                          "value": "application/json"
                        }
                      },
                      "body": "",
                      "schema": ""
                    }
                  ],
                  "responses": [
                    {
                      "name": "200",
                      "description": "",
                      "headers": {
                        "Content-Type": {
                          "value": "text/plain"
                        },
                        "X-My-Message-Header": {
                          "value": "42"
                        }
                      },
                      "body": "Hello World!\n",
                      "schema": ""
                    },
                    {
                      "name": "200",
                      "description": "",
                      "headers": {
                        "Content-Type": {
                          "value": "application/json"
                        },
                        "X-My-Message-Header": {
                          "value": "42"
                        }
                      },
                      "body": "{ \n  \"id\": 1,\n  \"message\": \"Hello World!\" \n}      \n",
                      "schema": ""
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "name": "Update a Message",
              "description": "",
              "method": "PUT",
              "parameters": {},
              "headers": {},
              "examples": [
                {
                  "name": "",
                  "description": "",
                  "requests": [
                    {
                      "name": "Update Plain Text Message",
                      "description": "",
                      "headers": {
                        "Content-Type": {
                          "value": "text/plain"
                        }
                      },
                      "body": "All your base are belong to us.\n",
                      "schema": ""
                    },
                    {
                      "name": "Update JSON Message",
                      "description": "",
                      "headers": {
                        "Content-Type": {
                          "value": "application/json"
                        }
                      },
                      "body": "{ \"message\": \"All your base are belong to us.\" }\n",
                      "schema": ""
                    }
                  ],
                  "responses": [
                    {
                      "name": "204",
                      "description": "",
                      "headers": {},
                      "body": "",
                      "schema": ""
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "All My Messages",
          "description": "A resource representing all of my messages in the system.\n\nWe have added the query URI template parameter - `limit`. This parameter is used for limiting the number of results returned by some actions on this resource. It does not affect every possible action of this resource therefore we will discuss it only at the particular action level below.\n \n",
          "uriTemplate": "/messages{?limit}",
          "model": {},
          "parameters": {},
          "headers": {},
          "actions": [
            {
              "name": "Retrieve all Messages",
              "description": "",
              "method": "GET",
              "parameters": {
                "limit": {
                  "description": "The maximum number of results to return.",
                  "type": "number",
                  "required": false,
                  "default": "20",
                  "example": "",
                  "values": []
                }
              },
              "headers": {},
              "examples": [
                {
                  "name": "",
                  "description": "",
                  "requests": [],
                  "responses": [
                    {
                      "name": "200",
                      "description": "",
                      "headers": {
                        "Content-Type": {
                          "value": "application/json"
                        }
                      },
                      "body": "[\n  {\n    \"id\": 1,\n    \"message\": \"Hello World!\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 2,\n    \"message\": \"Time is an illusion. Lunchtime doubly so.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 3,\n    \"message\": \"So long, and thanks for all the fish.\"\n  }\n]\n",
                      "schema": ""
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
